name-Apply branch policy, Apply branch security.

steps
1. Apply Branch Policy (for master)
🔹 1️⃣ Go to Azure DevOps Portal
Navigate to Repos > Branches

🔹 2️⃣ Find your branch (master)
Click ⋮ (ellipsis) next to it

Select Branch policies

🔹 3️⃣ Configure Policies:
Minimum number of reviewers → e.g. 1
Check for linked work items → optional
Limit merge types → e.g. Squash merge only

Build Validation →
Click + Add build policy
Select a pipeline
Set trigger type to Automatic
Optionally add Branch filters and Path filters


2. Apply Branch Security (for master)
🔹 1️⃣ Go to Azure DevOps Portal
Navigate to Repos > Branches

🔹 2️⃣ Find your branch (master)
Click ⋮ (ellipsis) next to it
Select Branch security

🔹 3️⃣ Set Permissions for Each Group:
For Contributors
  Contribute → Deny
  Force Push → Deny
  Manage Permissions → Not Set or Deny

For Project Administrators
  Contribute → Allow
  Force Push → Allow
  Manage Permissions → Allow


